Author: nymkappa#9440
Content:
Do you plan to allow the user to fill multiple swap using a single front-end order?
For example, in the order book there are the following swap request like this:
```
price  - max vol   -  receive
0.5 MORTY - 100 MORTY - 0.5 MORTY
0.5 MORTY - 200 MORTY - 0.5 MORTY
```

Author: nymkappa#9440
Content:
That would be really nice for the UX if I could fill both orders at the same time using a single actions from atomixDEX.
That would pretty much correspond to a `Market buy` filling as much order as needed until my maximum prices is reached.

So, the "Market swap order" would be:
```150 RICK for 300 MORTY```
And it would fill both pending swap request at once.

Author: jspook16#3059
Content: @jward01 Im not part of the team but have been following for a while. Atomicdex is essentially a wallet with a DEX interface. You can either import an existing komodo address wallet or create a new address wallet in atomicdex. If you import an existing wallet, your coins (compatible coins ~ 99% of existing coins) should be accessible to send, receive, or trade. If you create a new wallet you will have to send your coins to the new wallet address(es) (BTC will have a unique non kmd type address and so will some other type of coins that are not komodo asset chains). Once they are in your new wallet you can send, receive and trade as you wish. When you trade, BTC to ETH for example, you use the DEX functionality and create your order that you want to trade. When you go to place it, you can select from existing liquidity or create a new order at your desired rate. Once it is matched, the rest is taken care of automatically. It leaves your wallet and the traded assets are sent directly to your wallet. Pure awesome'ness from jl777 and Komodo Team.
